parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall while driving, making it difficult or impossible to restart, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the vehicle does not start
all electrical parts are working
including the battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heated/cool seat module can cause a burning smell, electrical issues, and other malfunctions, which can lead to a fire hazard or other safety risks.
symptoms: The heated/cool seat module is burning
there is an electrical smell
the ignition coil is malfunctioning
the 4-wheel drive system is malfunctioning
the windshield wiper motor linkage is malfunctioning
the transmission is malfunctioning
the engine light is on
the heated seats have stopped working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the automatic running boards can cause physical harm to the driver or passengers, as well as damage to the vehicle, due to the unexpected movement of the running boards.
symptoms: The running boards are retracting and lowering up and down while the vehicle is in motion
the running boards are making loud grinding sounds
the running boards are malfunctioning even when the vehicle is stopped with the engine off
the running boards can trap the driver's or passenger's foot
causing injury.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the auxiliary supply tube can cause coolant to leak, leading to engine overheating, damage to engine components, and potentially causing a loss of vehicle control or stalling, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Coolant leaking from the underbody of the vehicle
coolant leaking from the auxiliary supply tube
engine overheating
engine damage
loss of vehicle control
stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Wearing of Brake Rotors and Pads
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature wearing of brake rotors and pads can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake when the brake pedal is depressed, making it harder to come to a complete stop, which can lead to accidents or increase the stopping distance.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates when the brake pedal is depressed
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brakes make a grinding or screeching noise
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Transmission Control Module (TCM) can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden loss of acceleration, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission "seizes up" or fails to engage
the vehicle suddenly loses acceleration
the brakes lock up
the engine disengages from the drive train
the vehicle rolls backwards or loses control
abnormal noises are heard from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the mechatronic unit can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden loss of acceleration, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission "seizes up" or fails to engage
the vehicle suddenly loses acceleration
the brakes lock up
the engine disengages from the drive train
the vehicle rolls backwards or loses control
abnormal noises are heard from the transmission.
